  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6821.8 sitting right at the max positive gamma strike of 6820 (76.6B), dealers are aggressively selling into this rally to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX walls stacked from 6800-6830 suggests dealers will continue fade any upward momentum and provide buying support on dips toward the 6746 flip level. Watch for rejection at the 6820-6830 cluster where 152B in combined positive gamma creates a formidable ceiling, while any break below 6746 would shift dealers to short gamma and accelerate downside momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect the market to get capped near current levels with dealers selling the rally.",
